Come on. Sonny.
is that all you think about?

91
00:06:38.901 --> 00:06:41.607
- Freakin' A.
- (bell)

92
00:06:43.240 --> 00:06:44.865
Hey. guys. wait up.

93
00:06:44.993 --> 00:06:47.779
- Do I look OK. Frenchy?
- Sure. you look good.

94
00:06:47.912 --> 00:06:51.247
- I'm really nervous.
- You look terrific.

95
00:06:51.375 --> 00:06:55.289
- So. this is Rydell?
- Yep. You'll love it.

96
00:06:55.421 --> 00:06:59.253
I loved the last school I was at.
I wish I was there right now.

97
00:06:59.384 --> 00:07:01.875
Still. I'm no stranger to heartbreak.

98
00:07:02.012 --> 00:07:04.338
Why? You got psoriasis?

99
00:07:07.643 --> 00:07:09.139
(car backfires)

100
00:07:22.453 --> 00:07:24.494
Well. here we are again.

101
00:07:24.623 --> 00:07:28.537
- But this time we're seniors.
- We're gonna rule the school.

102
00:07:28.669 --> 00:07:30.543
(all laugh)

103
00:07:30.671 --> 00:07:32.498
Jan. that is so adolescent.

104
00:07:32.631 --> 00:07:36.167
- We are adolescent.
- We don't have to flaunt it.

105
00:07:36.304 --> 00:07:37.846
OK. girls.

106
00:07:37.971 --> 00:07:39.715
Let's go get 'em.

107
00:07:45.689 --> 00:07:47.931
Blanche. do you have
the new schedules?

108
00:07:48.067 --> 00:07:50.773
Yes. Miss McGee.
I just had my hands on them.

109
00:07:50.904 --> 00:07:53.774
Oh. good. they'll be
nice and smudged.

110
00:07:53.907 --> 00:07:57.657
Here we are. If it had been a snake.
it would've bitten me.

111
00:07:59.038 --> 00:08:02.372
These are the schedules
we couldn't find last semester.

112
00:08:02.500 --> 00:08:04.957
Next year.
you might find this semester's.

113
00:08:12.888 --> 00:08:16.838
- I've got Kenickie again.
- He's been here longer than I have.

114
00:08:16.976 --> 00:08:21.224
First day of school and already
my castor oil is missing.

115
00:08:22.191 --> 00:08:24.765
How many days
till Christmas vacation?

116
00:08:24.902 --> 00:08:26.017
86.

117
00:08:26.154 --> 00:08:28.112
- 86?
- And counting.

118
00:08:29.908 --> 00:08:32.315
- Can I help you?
- Yes. it's my first day.

119
00:08:32.453 --> 00:08:36.037
- I'm not sure where I should be.
- Welcome to Rydell.

120
00:08:36.166 --> 00:08:38.952
You'll have to fill out
these forms. but...

121
00:08:39.086 --> 00:08:41.756
Excuse me a minute.
I'll be right back.

122
00:08:43.592 --> 00:08:47.922
- Do you have a pencil. please?
- Yes. dear. There you are.

123
00:08:48.805 --> 00:08:50.301
(bell)

124
00:08:57.440 --> 00:09:01.190
Jeez. Every teacher I got this year
has flunked me at least once.

125
00:09:01.321 --> 00:09:03.776
You'll spend your time
in McGee's office.

126
00:09:03.906 --> 00:09:08.071
- She'll wish she'd never seen me.
- Yeah? And what are you gonna do?

127
00:09:08.204 --> 00:09:12.119
I just ain't gonna take her crap.
I don't take no crap from nobody.

128
00:09:12.250 --> 00:09:14.540
- Sonny?
- Oh. hello. ma'am.

129
00:09:14.670 --> 00:09:17.754
- Shouldn't you be in home room?
- I was going for a walk.

130
00:09:17.881 --> 00:09:20.041
- You were dawdling.
- Yes. ma'am.

131
00:09:20.176 --> 00:09:23.711
That is no way to start
a new semester. Mr LaTierri.

132
00:09:23.846 --> 00:09:25.258
(mutters in Italian)

133
00:09:25.391 --> 00:09:29.935
Perhaps a session of banging erasers
after school would put you on track.

134
00:09:30.063 --> 00:09:31.521
Yes. ma'am.

135
00:09:31.647 --> 00:09:35.481
- Do you plan to stand there all day?
- No. ma'am. I mean. yes.

136
00:09:35.611 --> 00:09:37.521
- Well. which is it?
- No. ma'am.

137
00:09:37.655 --> 00:09:39.898
- Good. Then move.
- Yes. ma'am.

138
00:09:42.494 --> 00:09:45.330
I'm glad you didn't take
any of her crap. Sonny.

139
00:09:45.456 --> 00:09:47.284
You would have told her off. huh?

140
00:09:47.417 --> 00:09:50.501
Mr LaTierri.
Yes. ma'am. no. ma'am...

141
00:09:50.629 --> 00:09:51.625
Hey. Eugene.

142
00:09:51.755 --> 00:09:53.748
How you doin'?

143
00:09:53.883 --> 00:09:56.126
- Shake. buddy.
- (buzzing)

144
00:09:56.677 --> 00:09:59.348
What's wrong?
You're wearing glasses.

145
00:09:59.473 --> 00:10:01.550
- I got an astigmatism.
- Too bad.

146
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:08.853
(students) # As I go travelling down
life's highway

147
00:10:09.402 --> 00:10:14.029
# Whatever course my fortunes
may foretell... 

148
00:10:15.200 --> 00:10:17.607
