The same? You can eat a lot.

724
00:51:29.636 --> 00:51:32.009
- You're funny.
- No. you are.

725
00:51:32.138 --> 00:51:36.387
- How ya doing. Zuke? Nice!
- Hiya. Rizzo. How are you?

726
00:51:36.519 --> 00:51:38.678
Peachy keen. jelly bean.

727
00:51:39.146 --> 00:51:42.350
You got any quarters?
We could split an Eskimo Pie.

728
00:51:42.484 --> 00:51:46.731
- My Dutch treat days are over.
- You plan on staying home a lot.

729
00:51:46.864 --> 00:51:50.484
Greetings. pals and gals.
Anybody got 23 cents?

730
00:51:50.619 --> 00:51:53.075
Wanna chip in for a Dog-Sled Delight?

731
00:51:53.205 --> 00:51:57.453
I don't know where my money goes.
A dime here. 1 5 cents there.

732
00:51:57.586 --> 00:52:00.706
In a couple of months
Frenchy can take us all out.

733
00:52:00.839 --> 00:52:02.583
A working girl with income.

734
00:52:02.717 --> 00:52:05.801
Y'know. they don't pay
that much to start with.

735
00:52:05.929 --> 00:52:09.974
It's more than we make. Ante up.
I don't get my allowance till Friday.

736
00:52:10.101 --> 00:52:12.592
- You get an allowance?
- When I'm a good boy.

737
00:52:12.728 --> 00:52:15.302
Viola. a Dog-Sled Delight
with four spoons.

738
00:52:15.440 --> 00:52:18.312
- And an Eskimo Pie with a knife.
- Hi. gang.

739
00:52:20.237 --> 00:52:22.397
Here you are. Grab it and growl.

740
00:52:26.494 --> 00:52:28.821
I got so many hickeys
I look like a leper.

741
00:52:28.956 --> 00:52:33.001
Cheer up. A hickey from Kenickie
is like a Hallmark card.

742
00:52:33.127 --> 00:52:35.369
You care enough
to send the very best.

743
00:52:37.008 --> 00:52:40.293
- You pig.
- I love it when you talk dirty.

744
00:52:41.721 --> 00:52:45.636
My parents want to invite you
to tea on Sunday. Will you come?

745
00:52:46.810 --> 00:52:50.015
- I don't like tea.
- You don't have to drink tea.

746
00:52:50.900 --> 00:52:52.938
Well. I don't like parents.

747
00:52:55.363 --> 00:52:57.736
- Want some?
- Erm. uh-uh.

748
00:52:57.866 --> 00:52:59.823
You sure are a cheap date.

749
00:52:59.951 --> 00:53:02.989
- I didn't mean it like that.
- I understand.

750
00:53:03.122 --> 00:53:06.621
- I always found you understanding.
- I am.

751
00:53:06.751 --> 00:53:10.667
I also think
there's more to you than just fat.

752
00:53:10.798 --> 00:53:13.502
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

753
00:53:13.634 --> 00:53:15.674
- Got a date for the dance-off?
- No.

754
00:53:15.803 --> 00:53:17.002
- Wanna go?
- Yeah.

755
00:53:17.138 --> 00:53:21.848
I'll be a senior forever if
I don't study for that algebra test.

756
00:53:21.978 --> 00:53:24.847
You're in luck.
You got an armed escort home.

757
00:53:24.981 --> 00:53:29.145
It's not the arms I'm worried about.
Sonny. It's the hands.

758
00:53:29.277 --> 00:53:31.270
She loves me.

759
00:53:33.324 --> 00:53:35.613
- You coming. French?
- I don't think so.

760
00:53:35.743 --> 00:53:38.828
- I think I'll hang out a bit longer.
- Alright.

761
00:53:38.955 --> 00:53:43.833
I have been dieting all day long. My
mom's apple pie's better than this.

762
00:53:43.962 --> 00:53:46.204
- Do you want a piece?
- Yeah. sure.

763
00:53:47.299 --> 00:53:48.628
- Putzie.
- Yeah?

764
00:53:48.759 --> 00:53:50.385
1 5 minutes!

765
00:53:51.804 --> 00:53:56.135
I'm worried about this dance-off. Do
they dance differently to back home?

766
00:53:56.268 --> 00:53:59.886
Don't worry.
Maybe we'll invent the Kangaroo Bop.

767
00:54:01.816 --> 00:54:03.857
Let's get out of here. Sandy.

768
00:54:03.985 --> 00:54:05.527
See you later.

769
00:54:06.280 --> 00:54:08.439
- Bye. Frenchy.
- See ya. Sandy.

770
00:54:10.993 --> 00:54:14.280
Great. I'm stuck with the check.
Give me money.

771
00:54:15.249 --> 00:54:19.199
OK. what's with you tonight?
You got the personality of a wet mop.

772
00:54:19.337 --> 00:54:23.419
- Don't start with me.
- Fine. How about I finish with ya?

773
00:54:24.217 --> 00:54:26.210
Finish this!

774
00:54:27.263 --> 00:54:28.806
To you from me. Pinky Lee.

775
00:54:31.643 --> 00:54:33.553
Sorry. French.

776
00:54:38.317 --> 00:54:40.988
(distant) Hey. Rizzo.
I want to talk to you!

777
00:54:43.824 --> 00:54:45.983
No use crying over spilt milk shake.

778
00:54:46.118 --> 00:54:47.863
Oh. I'll be OK.

779
00:54:49.581 --> 00:54:51.621
You know it's near closing time?

780
00:54:51.750 --> 00:54:53.827
Do you mind if I stay a bit longer?

781
00:54:53.961 --> 00:54:55.955
No. suit yourself.

782
00:54:56.089 --> 00:54:58.545
- Wow.
- What?

783
00:54:58.675 --> 00:55:02.045
I hate to tell you. but your
hair looks like an Easter egg.

784
00:55:02.931 --> 00:55:04.757
Oh. yeah.

785
00:55:04.890 --> 00:55:08.225
Well. I had a little trouble
in tinting class.

786
00:55:08.354 --> 00:55:11.639
In fact. I had a little trouble
in all my classes.

787
00:55:11.774 --> 00:55:15.109
Beauty school sure wasn't
what I thought it'd be.

788
00:55:15.237 --> 00:55:16.814
Nothing ever is.

789
00:55:20.660 --> 00:55:27.281
Vi? Erm. ... I dropped out.
What do you think of waitressing?

790
00:55:27.418 --> 00:55:29.376
You're too young to know.

791
00:55:30.254 --> 00:55:32.924
Maybe I could be
a telephone operator.

792
00:55:34.093 --> 00:55:37.924
No. I don't think I'd like to wear
those little things over my ears.

793
00:55:38.389 --> 00:55:43.764
God. if only I could have a guardian
angel to tell me what to do.

794
00:55:43.895 --> 00:55:47.515
Like Debbie Reynolds had in Tammy. 
What do you think?

795
00:55:48.610 --> 00:55:51.280
If you find him.
give him my phone number.

796
00:56:06.965 --> 00:56:10.251
# Your story's sad to tell

797
00:56:11.136 --> 00:56:14.838
# A teenage ne'er-do-well

798
00:56:15.809 --> 00:56:21.516
# Most mixed-up non-delinquent
on the block

799
00:56:23.192 --> 00:56:27.356
# Your future's so unclear now

800
00:56:27.907 --> 00:56:31.738
# What's left of your career now? 

801
00:56:32.370 --> 00:56:40.082
# Can't even get a trade-in
on your smock

802
00:56:55.356 --> 00:56:57.598
# Beauty school dropout

803
00:56:58.693 --> 00:57:01.897
# No graduation day for you

804
00:57:02.031 --> 00:57:04.070
# Beauty school dropout

805
00:57:05.159 --> 00:57:08.576
# Missed your midterms
and flunked shampoo

806
00:57:08.705 --> 00:57:11.790
# Well. at least
you could have taken time

807
00:57:11.917 --> 00:57:15.038
# To wash and clean your clothes up

808
00:57:15.171 --> 00:57:17.579
# After spending all that dough

809
00:57:17.715 --> 00:57:20.753
# To have the doctor fix your nose up

810
00:57:20.886 --> 00:57:22.843
# Baby. get movin'

811
00:57:24.223 --> 00:57:27.427
# Why keep your feeble hopes alive? 

812
00:57:27.561 --> 00:57:30.562
- # What are you provin'? 
- # What are you provin'? 

813
00:57:30.689 --> 00:57:34.106
# You've got the dream
but not the drive

814
00:57:34.235 --> 00:57:37.236
# If you go for your diploma

815
00:57:37.363 --> 00:57:40.282
# You could join a steno-pool

816
00:57:40.409 --> 00:57:42.449
# Turn in your teasing-comb

817
00:57:42.578 --> 00:57:45.579
# And go back to high school

818
00:57:49.794 --> 00:57:52.251
# Beauty school dropout

819
00:57:53.007 --> 00:57:55.712
# Hangin' around the corner store

820
00:57:55.844 --> 00:57:58.679
# Beauty school dropout

821
00:57:59.473 --> 00:58:02.807
# It's about time you knew the score

822
00:58:02.935 --> 00:58:05.641
# Well. they couldn't
teach you anything

823
00:58:06.273 --> 00:58:08.847
# You think you're such a looker

824
00:58:09.401 --> 00:58:12.439
# But no customer would go to you

825
00:58:12.572 --> 00:58:15.193
# Unless she was a hooker

826
00:58:20.248 --> 00:58:23.285
- # Baby. don't sweat it
- # Don't sweat it

827
00:58:23.418 --> 00:58:26.670
# You're not cut out to hold a job

828
00:58:26.798 --> 00:58:29.918
- # Better forget it
- # Forget it

829
00:58:30.051 --> 00:58:33.137
# Who wants their hair done
by a slob? 

830
00:58:33.264 --> 00:58:36.799
# Now your bangs are curled. 
your lashes twirled

831
00:58:36.934 --> 00:58:39.604
# But still the world is cruel

832
00:58:39.730 --> 00:58:41.888
# Wipe off that angel face

833
00:58:42.024 --> 00:58:44.349
# And go back to high school

834
00:58:46.112 --> 00:58:47.773
# Baby. don't blow it

835
00:58:49.448 --> 00:58:52.451
# Don't put my good advice to shame

836
00:58:52.578 --> 00:58:54.617
# Baby. you know it

837
00:58:55.915 --> 00:58:59.201
# Even Dear Abby would say the same

838
00:58:59.336 --> 00:59:02.669
# Now. I've called the shot. 
get off the pot

839
00:59:02.798 --> 00:59:07.343
# I've really got to fly

840
00:59:08.430 --> 00:59:14.303
# Gotta be going to that malt shop

841
00:59:14.436 --> 00:59:20.891
# In the sky

842
00:59:25.325 --> 00:59:28.243
# Beauty school dropout

843
00:59:28.370 --> 00:59:30.909
# Go back to high school

844
00:59:31.666 --> 00:59:34.583
# Beauty school dropout

845
00:59:34.711 --> 00:59:37.333
# Go back to high school

846
00:59:37.923 --> 00:59:40.924
# Beauty school dropout

847
00:59:41.051 --> 00:59:45.098
# Go back to high school

848
00:59:57.405 --> 01:00:00.323
- Lower your head. Kenickie.
- What are you doing?

849
01:00:00.451 --> 01:00:02.822
- Give him a break.
- Oh. I will!

850
01:00:02.953 --> 01:00:05.528
No. we'll work on the brakes later.

851
01:00:05.665 --> 01:00:07.324
Move over. slick.

852
01:00:07.458 --> 01:00:09.416
Fruitcake. you got it on backwards.

853
01:00:09.544 --> 01:00:12.215
- What car did you swipe it from?
- Your mother's.

854
01:00:20.682 --> 01:00:22.225
Rizz.

855
01:00:29.234 --> 01:00:32.022
Can you believe it?
Nationwide television!

856
01:00:35.533 --> 01:00:38.619
- How you doing?
- Still gonna go to the dance?

857
01:00:38.746 --> 01:00:41.913
Man. I'm gonna have
the hottest date there.

858
01:00:42.876 --> 01:00:46.542
Biggest thing to happen to Rydell
and we don't have dates.

859
01:00:46.672 --> 01:00:49.673
- Maybe Rudi from the Capri Lounge?
- Get serious.

860
01:00:49.800 --> 01:00:52.422
- It's a suggestion.
- I already called him.

861
01:00:59.186 --> 01:01:01.856
Relax. I think our luck is changing.

862
01:01:08.781 --> 01:01:10.821
Do you know what you're doing?

863
01:01:10.950 --> 01:01:13.109
What we're doing. Come on.

864
01:01:42.863 --> 01:01:44.738
Hey. Marty. Lookin' good.

865
01:01:46.325 --> 01:01:49.197
Would you just excuse me one second?

866
01:01:51.832 --> 01:01:53.991
Feelin' good. too. huh?

867
01:01:54.126 --> 01:01:56.701
Sonny. There he is. Vince Fontaine.

868
01:01:56.839 --> 01:01:58.998
I seen better heads on a mug of beer.

869
01:01:59.133 --> 01:02:04.009
- Grow up. He's the living end.
- Yeah. if you like older guys.

870
01:02:17.362 --> 01:02:18.941
Danny. this is so exciting.

871
01:02:19.073 --> 01:02:21.742
You gotta make friends
with the cameraman.

872
01:02:21.867 --> 01:02:24.026
- You know him?
- His name's Ted.

873
01:02:25.248 --> 01:02:26.871
Doody. how do I look?

874
01:02:26.998 --> 01:02:30.664
Like a beautiful blonde pineapple.

875
01:02:33.048 --> 01:02:35.622
You're late. fellas. Where you been?

876
01:02:35.759 --> 01:02:39.175
- The gym never looked so good.
- You bring the provisions?

877
01:02:39.304 --> 01:02:41.547
Alright. kids. I want a big circle.

878
01:02:44.353 --> 01:02:48.352
Come on. boys and girls.
we are going on the air very shortly.

879
01:02:48.483 --> 01:02:54.071
But first. some warm-up numbers
with Johnny Casino and the Gamblers.

880
01:03:02.124 --> 01:03:07.001
# Oh. baby. rock'n'roll
is here to stay. it will never die

881
01:03:07.964 --> 01:03:12.009
# It was meant to be that way. 
though I don't know why

882
01:03:12.469 --> 01:03:17.133
# I don't care what people say
Rock'n'roll is here to stay

883
01:03:17.267 --> 01:03:21.811
# We don't care what people say
Rock'n'roll is here to stay

884
01:03:21.939 --> 01:03:25.984
# Everybody rock. everybody rock

885
01:03:26.736 --> 01:03:30.486
# Everybody rock. everybody rock

886
01:03:31.243 --> 01:03:33.199
# Come on

887
01:03:33.327 --> 01:03:35.155
# Everybody rock

888
01:03:35.831 --> 01:03:40.161
# If you don't like rock'n'roll. 
think what you'd be missin'

889
01:03:40.794 --> 01:03:44.959
# If you like to bop and stroll. 
come on down and listen

890
01:03:45.091 --> 01:03:47.464
# Let's all start to have a ball

891
01:03:47.594 --> 01:03:49.883
# Everybody rock'n'roll

892
01:03:58.941 --> 01:04:01.433
- What are their names?
- Fred and Ginger.

893
01:04:01.569 --> 01:04:03.362
Fred and Ginger.

894
01:04:26.808 --> 01:04:31.470
- I hope I don't get camera fright.
- Don't worry. we'll be cool.

895
01:04:31.604 --> 01:04:33.479
- Yeah?
- Don't worry?

896
01:04:33.607 --> 01:04:35.435
Good. Come on. let's go.

897
01:04:38.195 --> 01:04:41.816
# What's that playing on the radio? 

898
01:04:41.951 --> 01:04:45.783
# Why do I start swaying to and fro? 

899
01:04:45.913 --> 01:04:49.616
# I have never heard
that song before

900
01:04:49.752 --> 01:04:53.287
# But if I don't hear it any more... 

901
01:04:53.422 --> 01:04:55.581
Why not let me lead for a change?

902
01:04:55.717 --> 01:04:57.756
I can't help it. I'm used to leadin'.

903
01:04:57.886 --> 01:04:59.429
OK.

904
01:05:01.766 --> 01:05:05.182
Doody. can't you
turn me around or something?

905
01:05:05.311 --> 01:05:07.768
Don't talk. Frenchy.
I'm trying to count.

906
01:05:08.649 --> 01:05:10.690
# A melody

907
01:05:10.818 --> 01:05:12.479
# That's never the same

908
01:05:12.612 --> 01:05:15.400
# A melody
that's calling your name... 

909
01:05:15.532 --> 01:05:18.533
Have you thought
of singing professionally?

910
01:05:18.660 --> 01:05:20.701
# (off key) Come back to me-e-e

911
01:05:20.830 --> 01:05:23.404
- # Please... 
- Hey. Zuko! Zuke!

912
01:05:23.543 --> 01:05:26.115
I want you
to meet Cha Cha di Gregorio.

913
01:05:26.253 --> 01:05:28.542
- How you doing. baby?
- Fine.

914
01:05:28.673 --> 01:05:29.752
Who is she?

915
01:05:29.883 --> 01:05:34.095
They call me Cha Cha. cos I'm
the best dancer at St Bernadette's.

916
01:05:34.221 --> 01:05:37.388
With the worst reputation.

917
01:05:37.516 --> 01:05:39.509
Let's go. Sandy.

918
01:05:39.644 --> 01:05:43.643
- Who's that girl?
- Just a girl I know. that's all.

919
01:05:49.949 --> 01:05:51.490
Hi.

920
01:05:52.659 --> 01:05:54.285
I'm Vince Fontaine.

921
01:05:55.121 --> 01:05:58.454
Do your folks know
I come into your room every night?

922
01:05:58.583 --> 01:06:00.742
Over KZAZ. that is.

923
01:06:03.714 --> 01:06:05.956
I'm judging the dance contest.

924
01:06:06.092 --> 01:06:07.801
I don't think I'm entered.

925
01:06:07.928 --> 01:06:10.882
A knockout like you?
What's your name?

926
01:06:11.015 --> 01:06:13.341
- Marty.
- Marty what?

927
01:06:13.476 --> 01:06:16.892
Maraschino. You know. like in cherry.

928
01:06:40.634 --> 01:06:43.302
- What are you doing?
- Washing my hands.

929
01:06:44.596 --> 01:06:47.717
# You don't remember me

930
01:06:47.850 --> 01:06:50.305
# But I remember you

931
01:06:50.437 --> 01:06:53.224
# It was not so long ago

932
01:06:53.356 --> 01:06:55.350
# You broke my heart in two

933
01:06:55.484 --> 01:06:58.154
# Tears on my pillow

934
01:06:58.779 --> 01:07:00.690
# Pain in my heart

935
01:07:00.824 --> 01:07:04.158
# Caused by you. 
you. you. you. you... 

936
01:07:04.286 --> 01:07:06.244
How do you know her?

937
01:07:06.372 --> 01:07:09.788
Erm. she's an old friend
of the family. that's all.

938
01:07:10.627 --> 01:07:13.118
# Love is not a toy

939
01:07:13.255 --> 01:07:15.961
# When you find the one you love... 

940
01:07:16.093 --> 01:07:18.879
- Aren't you glad to be back?
- Oh. yeah.

941
01:07:19.012 --> 01:07:21.682
Besides. blondes do have more fun.

942
01:07:22.642 --> 01:07:25.346
# If we could start anew

943
01:07:25.478 --> 01:07:27.518
# I wouldn't hesitate... 

944
01:07:29.857 --> 01:07:32.943
When I hear music.
I can't make my feet behave.

945
01:07:33.070 --> 01:07:35.859
- Thinks she's Tinker Bell.
- Hush. Sonny.

946
01:07:36.490 --> 01:07:38.900
# Pain in my heart

947
01:07:39.036 --> 01:07:40.994
# Caused by you

948
01:07:41.622 --> 01:07:43.781
# You-ou-ou-ou

949
01:07:45.919 --> 01:07:48.493
Sshh.

950
01:07:48.630 --> 01:07:50.872
The Rydell fight song!

951
01:08:14.578 --> 01:08:16.950
When you are finished...

952
01:08:18.040 --> 01:08:22.619
You will be happy to know that
I am not judging the dance contest.

953
01:08:27.844 --> 01:08:30.417
I think we all owe
a round of applause

954
01:08:30.555 --> 01:08:34.175
to Patty Simcox and Eugene Felznik
and committee

955
01:08:34.310 --> 01:08:36.635
for their beautiful decorations.

956
01:08:36.770 --> 01:08:38.894
Let's hear it for the toilet paper.

957
01:08:42.653 --> 01:08:47.814
In a few moments. the entire nation
will be watching Rydell High.

958
01:08:47.951 --> 01:08:52.198
God help us. and I want you all
to be on your best behaviour.

959
01:08:52.331 --> 01:08:54.324
No heinie-biting.

960
01:08:56.085 --> 01:08:57.745
And now. here he is.

961
01:08:57.879 --> 01:08:59.707
the Prince of the Platters.

962
01:08:59.840 --> 01:09:02.295
Mr Vince Fontaine.

963
01:09:08.933 --> 01:09:11.604
Mr Vince Fontaine?

964
01:09:24.160 --> 01:09:25.988
(drum rolls)

965
01:09:35.757 --> 01:09:39.341
